-- Terra Firma Nears Exclusive Garden Centre Talks, Times Says
-- B y   A n n e - S y l v a i n e   C h a s s a n y
-- 2012-01-29T11:54:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-29/terra-firma-nears-exclusive-talks-on-garden-centre-times-says.html
Terra Firma Capital Partners Ltd.,
the private equity firm owned by Guy Hands, is close to buying
the Garden Centre Group, the Sunday Times said, citing an
unidentified source close to the sale.  Terra Firma is expected this week to enter exclusive talks
with the sellers, which include  Lloyds Banking Group Plc (LLOY) , and a
deal would value the company at 300 million pounds ($471
million), according to the newspaper.  Andrew Dowler , a spokesman for London-based Terra Firma,
and Nicole Sharp, a spokeswoman for Lloyds, declined to comment
to Bloomberg News today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
